name: Nil Ultra: War and Porno (Obvious Choices)
description: Each limited edition print in Hit City U.S.A.'s artist series is 11" x 14", printed high quality digitally, hand signed signed and numbered out of 25, authenticated with a Hit City seal, and comes with a special "Nice Touch" mixtape from the artist. Printing and framing all done in Downtown Los Angeles. How do you carve an elephant from stone? You take a large piece of stone and take away everything that is not an elephant. ...Unless you've been convinced that stone isn't really the best material for your purpose. Are you sure you even want an elephant? Maybe you're thinking of a rhino. Jason Moore is great at turning elephants into rhinos. (Rhinos are usually the way to go by the way.) Please allow a month for delivery of framed prints. Hand-delivery available within Los Angeles.

name: Hannah Hooper: Untitled
description: Each limited edition print in Hit City U.S.A.'s artist series is 11" x 14", printed high quality digitally, hand signed signed and numbered out of 25, authenticated with a Hit City seal, and comes with a special "Nice Touch" mixtape from the artist. Printing and framing all done in Downtown Los Angeles. Hannah Hooper is an American artist and musician based out of Los Angeles. Her work deals with a diverse array of subject matter including tragic pop culture figures, claustrophobic beach/crowd scenes and strange figures distorted through bodies of water. Hannah is almost obsessive in her ever-present need to draw. She's filled countless sketchbooks with studies of her surroundings, tours, friends/family and imaginary landscapes. As a member of Grouplove, Hannah has also taken on the role of art director for the band. Her work adorns virtually all of the albums, posters, merch and even the costume and stage design. The frenetic energy of her mark making and line-work echoes the inspired and frenzied performances of the group. 'I can never sit still' -Hannah Hooper After graduating with a BFA from Parson's School of Design, Hannah cut her teeth in New York's Lower East Side art scene during the 2000s, rubbing elbows with some of today's most notable younger contemporary artists. In 2007, with Christian Zucchoni at her side, Hannah travelled to Crete for an intensive painting residency, where they soon met the other members of what would become Grouplove. Hannah now resides in LA, plays music with Grouplove and maintains a robust and multi-faceted studio practice on and off tour. These high quality digital prints are 11" x 14", hand signed by the artist and numbered out of 25. Please allow a month for delivery of framed prints. Hand-delivery available within Los Angeles.

name: Hassan Rahim: White Lighter
description: Each limited edition print in Hit City U.S.A.'s artist series is 11" x 14", printed high quality digitally, hand signed signed and numbered out of 25, authenticated with a Hit City seal, and comes with a special "Nice Touch" mixtape from the artist. Printing and framing all done in Downtown Los Angeles. Hassan Rahim b. 1987, Los Angeles. Hassan Rahim is an artist and art director living and working in Los Angeles. His work, reminiscent of vague childhood memories and adolescent fantasies, utilizes photography, collage and mixed media to create strong contextual pieces which are both appealing and alarming to the audience. When his works are viewed as a whole, his obsessions become evident—marble surfaces, hoop dreams, deconstructed portraits of quick-to-rise idols, and the overdone opulence associated with mid-90s celebrity athletes, executed in a manner that often exudes a sense of darkness within its message. These high quality digital prints are 11" x 14", hand signed by the artist and numbered out of 25. Please allow a month for delivery of framed prints. Hand-delivery available within Los Angeles.

name: Hit City U.S.A. Bandana
description: These Hit City U.S.A. bandanas were specially tailored to flawlessly line your pockets and wipe dirt off your beautiful faces with nothing but class. Available in two color schemes: navy with burgundy trim, and red with navy trim. Manufactured locally in California.

name: Darren Weiss (PAPA): The Only Thing Worse Than A Woman Is A Man
description:
Darren Weiss is a writer, artist and musician from Los Angeles, CA. This is his first collection of poetry and drawings. As singer and drummer of the band PAPA, his works include the Tender Madness LP and the A Good Woman is Hard to Find EP. 

The Only Thing Worse Than a Woman is a Man is a collection of Weiss' poetry and drawings over the past three years, pulled mostly from notebooks he keeps as a totem on the road.

name: Sterling Bartlett: HCUSA Metal Mix
description: With Hit City U.S.A.'s "Nice Touch" mix tape series, we bring our best friends onboard to put their magic touch to cassette. Trust that taste, listen, love, learn something new. Track lists not included. Drawing upon an authoritative understanding of americana, heavy metal, punk rock, skateboarding, and fringe culture at large, Sterling Bartlett has crafted a meticulous visual language loaded with double entendre and pictorial pun. Boutique street wear brands, skate companies, recording artists, and multinational corporations alike have called upon his expertise to solve visual problems and lend cultural cache. In addition to his sought-after hand illustration work, Sterling regularly provides art direction, creative direction, marketing strategies, and brand consultation for a diverse clientele. His work has been featured in Entertainment Weekly, The Pitchfork Review, Fast Company, Bullett Magazine, Juxtapoz.com, Beautiful/Decay, Transworld Skateboarding, Color Magazine, and Antenna.
